        visualCue: "Picture three starting method graphs side by side: DOL shows a huge current spike at t=0; star-delta shows a smaller spike then a second smaller spike at changeover; VSD shows a smooth ramp from zero — like easing a car away from traffic lights versus flooring the accelerator."
