        visualCue: "Imagine an ohmmeter with leads placed at two ends of an earth conductor: a reading of 0.32 Ω shows a solid, low-resistance connection. The same test on a corroded lug returns 4.8 Ω — well above acceptable — flagging a joint that must be remade."
