        visualCue: "Visualise a truss node: a gusset plate connects three angles — the bottom chord, a diagonal, and a vertical. Fillet welds run along each angle leg on both sides of the gusset. An inset cross-section of the fillet weld shows the leg size (6 mm), the throat (4.2 mm = 0.707 × 6), and the fusion faces."
